    <stitle>STARTING MOTORS - CLEANING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="clean" graphiccount="0">
        <title>CLEANING</title>
        <para>Never clean the drive, armature and fields in any degreasing tank or with grease dissolving solvents. Such
            action will dissolve the lubricant in the drive and damage the insulation in the armature and field coils.
            All parts except the drive should be cleaned with mineral spirits and a brush. The drive can be wiped with a
            clean cloth.
        </para>
        <para>If the commutator is dirty it may be cleaned with No.00 sandpaper.
            <emph type="bold">Never use emery cloth to clean the commutator.</emph>
        </para>
    </svcproc>
